    h1.heading Swiftoberfest Contest Rules

  h5 Join and compete in the Topcoder iOS Developer Community to connect and engage with your peers across the globe, receive feedback on your work from the most successful iOS developers and designers, and showcase your talent while building real-world applications to win prizes along the way.

  ol
    li
      p
        span.title Eligibility:

        | The Swiftoberfest Contest (“Contest”) is open to legal residents of United States who part of the iOS Developer Community (an exclusive segment of Appirio’s Topcoder community) prior to the Contest start date (“Contestants”).   Contest is void wherever restricted or prohibited by law.  Contest is sponsored by Appirio, 760 Market Street, 11th Floor, San Francisco, CA 94102 (“Sponsor”).  Employees and immediate families of Sponsor (“Contest Entity”) and their respective parents, subsidiaries, affiliates, directors, owners, employees and agents are not eligible.  This Contest is subject to all applicable federal, state and local laws.

      p The Contest Submission Period begins on October 5, 2015 at 12:01 a.m. Pacific Daylight Time (“PDT”), and ends on December 31, 2015 at 11:59 p.m. PST (the “Contest Submission Period”). Within the Contest Submission Period there will be three (3) monthly contests (the “Monthly Contest Submission Period”) and one (1) overall contest that combines the winning points of the three monthly contests according to the schedule below.

