      p Points will only be awarded for a member’s highest ranking entry for any single challenge.

      p The top scorers in each month will be deemed winners (“Selected Contestant(s)”). For October, there will be 5 winners.  For November and December, there will be 3 winners each month.

      p In the event of a tie during scoring, the Contestant who achieved the highest score first, shall be deemed the Selected Contestant.

      p There will be an overall leaderboard and a monthly leaderboard posted on #[a(href="http://ios.topcoder.com/") www.ios.topcoder.com] that show the points members have earned from competing in challenges.  The monthly leaderboard resets at the beginning of each Monthly Contest Submission Period, but the Overall winner will be determined by the aggregate points value of all leaderboards during the Contest Period.

      p Selected Contestants may be sent a declaration of eligibility / liability / publicity release (“Release”).  Unless restricted by law, each Selected Contestant will be required to complete and return the Release within seventy-two (72) hours of the date notice is sent.

