      p
        span.title Winner Notification:

        | On or about 12 days after the close of each Contest Submission Period, Selected Contestants will be contacted using the information provided in their account.  The Selected Contestant will be required to respond (as directed) within 3 days of attempted notification.  Selected Entrant’s failure to respond timely to the Notification may result in forfeiture of the Prize, and in such case, Sponsor may award the prize to the next highest scoring entry from among the remaining Qualified Submissions, up to three (3) times. The Selected Contestant may be sent a declaration of eligibility / liability / publicity release (“Release”).  Except where prohibited by law, the Release will state that Selected Contestant agrees to allow Sponsor to use (without additional compensation) his or her name, address, photograph, testimonial, likeness and/or biographical information for purposes of advertising and promotion (including, without limitation, posting on Sponsor’s website(s) and affiliated website(s)). Selected Contestants may also be required to provide name, U.S. Social Security Number (for tax form purposes), birth date, current address, and phone number.  Unless restricted by law, the Selected Contestants will be required to complete and return the Release within the time period specified therein. The Prize may be forfeited, if the Selected Contestant  (i) cannot be reached; (ii) does not respond to the Notification in a timely manner as required pursuant to these Official Rules; (iii) fails to obtain all signatures on the Release and to return the documents in a timely manner as required pursuant to these Official Rules; or (iv) cannot accept or receive the Prize for any reason. Non-compliance with these Official Rules may result in disqualification and selection of an alternate Selected Entrant.  Sponsor may not make multiple attempts to contact Selected Entrants. Winning a prize is a taxable event.  In some cases, depending upon the prize value, the Selected Contestant may be sent a form 1099 for tax purposes.

